### 1. No global error handling
A thrown error or rejected promise in any handler will crash the process or leak stack traces.

### 2. No input validation / no parameterized routes yet
The `/users` route is static, but as soon as you add `/users/:id` or POST bodies, you'll need validation.

### 3. Missing security middleware
No `helmet`, no rate limiting, no body size limits, no CORS policy.

### 4. Information disclosure
