| Concern | Fix |
|---|---|
| Header hardening | `helmet()`, `disable('x-powered-by')` |
| DoS / brute force | `express-rate-limit` + JSON body size limit |
| Injection / bad input | `zod` schema validation on query/body |
| Information disclosure | Generic 500 body; stack trace only in logs; PII stripped |
| Config hygiene | `process.env.PORT` with numeric coercion |
| Reliability | Global error middleware + `unhandledRejection` / `uncaughtException` hooks |
| Operational safety | Graceful `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` shutdown |

### Additional recommendations (not shown)
- Add authN (JWT/session) and authZ before any endpoint that returns user data.
- Use `pino` or `winston` with request IDs instead of `console.*`.
- Add CSRF protection if cookies/sessions are ever introduced.
- Add CORS with an explicit origin allowlist if this is consumed cross-origin.
- Run `npm audit` / Dependabot in CI; pin dependencies.
- Add integration tests for the 400/404/500 paths to lock in the contract.

