Here's a review of the current code with security-focused improvements for error handling and input validation.

## Current Issues

### 1. No global error handling
Express will silently swallow async errors and leak stack traces in default error responses.

### 2. No security headers
Missing standard hardening (CSP, X-Frame-Options, HSTS, etc.).

### 3. No input validation
`/users` currently takes no input, but there's no framework in place for when routes are added (e.g., `/users/:id`).

### 4. No rate limiting
Endpoints are open to abuse/DoS.

### 5. Hardcoded port & no graceful shutdown
Port `3000` is hardcoded; no SIGTERM/SIGINT handling.

### 6. No body parser limits
When POST routes are added, large payloads could exhaust memory.

### 7. PII exposure
`/users` returns email addresses unconditionally with no auth.

