|---|---|
| Header leakage / clickjacking / XSS | `helmet()` + `disable('x-powered-by')` |
| Brute force / DoS | `express-rate-limit` |
| Oversized payloads | `limit: '10kb'` on body parsers |
| Untrusted input | `express-validator` with strict schemas + generic 400 responses |
| Stack-trace disclosure | Centralized error handler returns generic messages; logs stay server-side |
| Unhandled promise rejections | `process.on('unhandledRejection' / 'uncaughtException')` |
| PII exposure | Return only non-sensitive fields; add auth before exposing `email` |
| Config hardcoding | `process.env.PORT` with safe `Number()` cast |
| Zombie connections on deploy | `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` → `server.close()` |

