const idSchema = z.coerce.number().int().positive();

app.get('/users/:id', (req, res, next) => {
  const parsed = idSchema.safeParse(req.params.id);
  if (!parsed.success) return res.status(400).json({ error: 'Invalid id' });
  // ...
});
```

## 3. Security best practices

**Missing hardening:**

| Concern | Fix |
|---|---|
| Missing security headers (XSS, clickjacking, MIME sniffing) | `app.use(helmet())` |
| No rate limiting — trivial to DoS | `express-rate-limit` on all routes, stricter on auth/write routes |
| No CORS policy — relies on default allow | `cors({ origin: <allowlist>, credentials: false })` |
