| Security headers | `helmet()` + `x-powered-by` disabled | Mitigates common header-based attacks, hides framework |
| DoS protection | `express-rate-limit` + `json({ limit: '10kb' })` | Limits request rate and payload size |
| PII | Removed `email` from default `/users` response | Principle of least disclosure |
| 404 handling | Explicit JSON 404 handler | Consistent API contract, no HTML leakage |
| Test-friendliness | `app.listen` gated on `require.main === module` | Avoids side effects when imported by tests |
| Graceful shutdown | `SIGTERM`/`SIGINT` handlers that call `server.close()` | Clean connection draining in container environments |

