## Key Security Points

| Concern | Mitigation |
|---|---|
| XSS / clickjacking / MIME sniffing | `helmet()` sets CSP, X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, Referrer-Policy, HSTS |
| DoS via large bodies | `express.json({ limit: '10kb' })` |
| Brute force / scraping | `express-rate-limit` |
| Injection via path/query params | `express-validator` with strict types + `.toInt()` coercion |
| Info disclosure | `x-powered-by` disabled; generic 500 response; no `err.stack` to client |
| Unsafe binding | Default `HOST=127.0.0.1`; set explicitly in prod behind a proxy |
| Hanging requests on deploy | `server.close()` in SIGTERM/SIGINT handlers |
| Crash on async errors | `unhandledRejection` / `uncaughtException` handlers + centralized error middleware |

---

